cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY 

The paper discusses a system that combines self-organized map (SOM) properties with spiking neural networks (SNNs) for unsupervised learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). However, given the focus on neural networks and unsupervised learning, cs.NE and cs.LG are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses classification tools, which could potentially place it in cs.AI or cs.CV. Finally, the use of inhibition strategies and biologically-inspired approaches suggests a potential fit with cs.SY.
